With this action you can set the position for the given sequence element in the room. You supply the sequence element ID (as returned by the action Create Sequence), and then the new X and Y position. If you tick the "relative" checkbox, then the values given for X and Y will be added to the current sequence position, otherwise they will be an absolute position.
The ID of the sequence element to set the position of.
The new x position in the room for the sequence.
The new y position in the room for the sequence.

The above action block code retrieves the current position of the sequence element ID stored in the variable "my_seq". These vales are then used to set the position of the sequence, moving it 10 pixels to the right.
